    "comment": "Rationale: \"The ectopic expression of eGFP-Ago2WT together with tdTomato allowed us to compare the effects of NMDA application on Ago2 levels in spines versus dendrites. Similar to dendrites (Fig. 4A), we found that eGFP-Ago2 levels are also decreased in spines upon NMDA-R activation (Fig. 5, A and B). Interestingly, when comparing the turnover of eGFP-Ago2 in spines versus dendrites, we observed a greater decrease of Ago2 in spines compared with dendrites after NMDA-R stimulation (Fig. 5, C and D).\". Experimental description: M&M: \"pEGFP-Ago2WT was cloned by inserting human Ago2 from pcDNA3-myc-Ago2 (31) into the pEGFP-C2 vector (Clontech).\"",
